13 December 2019 - The scene where Rashied Staggie was shot. JOHANNESBURG - Western Cape Police have launched a manhunt for the murderer of former ‘Hard Livings’ gang leader Rashied Staggie. WATCH: Police can't confirm Mitchells Plain murder linked to that of Staggie The 58-year-old died on Friday after he was shot outside his home in Salt River on Friday. Staggie's twin brother, Rashaad was shot and set alight by a vigilante group People Against Gangsterism and Drugs (PAGAD) in 1996.